"```sql\nSELECT \n    (COUNT(CASE WHEN Segment = 'Premium' THEN 1 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) AS PercentageOfPremiumGasStations\nFROM \n    gasstations\nWHERE \n    Country = 'SVK';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of gas stations in Slovakia that are classified as \"Premium.\" It does this by counting the number of gas stations with the \"Premium\" segment and dividing it by the total number of gas stations in Slovakia, then multiplying by 100 to get the percentage."